<div class="headerbox">
<h3>December 19, 2012</h3>  
</div>
<div>
We&rsquo;re only twenty days away from the world&rsquo;s largest annual innovation event! And now, with an all-time new record of more than 1.85 million net square feet of show floor space, it&rsquo;s time for you to solidify your plans! From newly added keynote addresses to conference passes and show floor tours, this edition of<em> CES Up to the Minute </em>is filled with tons of valuable information. 






</div>

<br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="928"><span style="display: none">New Keynote Addresses Just Added!</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">New Keynote Addresses Just Added!</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/attendee/BrandMatters_Tag_Spon_color.gif"/>
<p>As the consumer technology industry continues to reinvent itself with stunning speed in a mobile world, who will be at the forefront of the next wave of big ideas and must-have products? The <a href="http://cesweb.org/Events/Keynotes.aspx"><u>Next Generation of Innovators keynote</u></a> panel will introduce you to several Founder CEOs who just might have created the &ldquo;next big thing.&rdquo; Join moderator Jeff Jordan, entrepreneur and tech exec, now partner at Silicon Valley&rsquo;s hottest VC firm, as he explores the trials and potential rewards ahead for some of tech&rsquo;s hottest young innovators. Hear from these up-and-coming entrepreneurs at 11 a.m. Tuesday, January 8 in the LVH Theater.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
<a href="http://cesweb.org/Brand-Matters/Keynotes-Events.aspx"><u>Marketing in the Cloud, the Brand Matters keynote address</u></a>, kicks off with a fireside chat between Michael Kassan, CEO of MediaLink and Marc Benioff, CEO of Salesforce.com, the Brand Matters keynote address will focus on the new frontier of marketing. Kassan and Benioff will then be joined by a panel of marketing executives from American Express, AT&amp;T, Coca Cola, Unilever and Samsung to continue the thought-provoking discussion. You won&rsquo;t want to miss this keynote taking place at 11 a.m. Wednesday, January 9 in the LVH Theater.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
How your consumers are REALLY engaging with digital media, is the topic of discussion at the <a href="http://cesweb.org/Brand-Matters/Keynotes-Events.aspx"><u>Brand Matters SuperSession</u></a>. MediaLink, in collaboration with The Intelligence Group, brings together a panel of young people who will be asked about their media consumption habits, and in the process begin to unearth the social, cultural, technology and media forces that are making them increasingly elusive for most marketers. Immediately following this panel of young consumers, executives from major brands such as Twitter, Foursquare, Tumblr, YouTube, Facebook and Amazon will respond in real-time to what they just heard. This fascinating SuperSession will take place </p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="909"><span style="display: none">Living in Digital Times Brings High Profile Speakers to CES</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Living in Digital Times Brings High Profile Speakers to CES</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/attendee/lidt.gif"/>
<p><p>
 <span style="font-size: 12px;">Living in Digital Times will deliver an elite line-up of health care professionals, journalists, university professors, entrepreneurs and innoLiving in Digital Times will deliver an elite line-up of health care professionals, journalists, university professors, entrepreneurs and innovators to the 2013 CES conference program. You won&rsquo;t want to miss a minute of these provocative discussions.</span><br />
 <strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;</span></strong><br />
 <span style="font-size: 12px;">CNN&rsquo;s<strong> <strong>Dr. Sanjay Gupta</strong></strong> kicks off the <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx#TrackDHTH"><u>Digital Health Summit</u></a> on January 9 and 10 from 9 a.m. &ndash; 5 p.m., with &ldquo;Digital Health Confidential,&rdquo; setting the pace for a thought-provoking, informative and jam-packed two-day conference.</span><br />
 <strong>&nbsp;<br />
 <strong>Vinton Cerf,</strong> </strong>Chief Internet Evangelist for Google will deliver the keynote address, &ldquo;How the Internet and Users Have Grown Up Together&rdquo; at the <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx#TrackSilvers"><u>Silvers Summit</u></a> 9 a.m. Tuesday, January 8.<br />
 <strong>&nbsp;<br />
 <strong>Walter Mossberg</strong>, </strong>Personal Technology Columnist, <em>The Wall Street Journal, </em>will kick-off the <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx#TrackHET"><u>HigherEdTECH Summit</u></a><a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx#TrackHET"> </a>by offering his unique perspective on what new technology will emerge in 2013.<br />
 <strong>&nbsp;<br />
 <strong>Lawrence H. Summers</strong>, </strong>the Charles W. Eliot University Professor and President Emeritus at Harvard University will close out the summit by sharing his vision on what it will take to educate the next generation of entrepreneurs. The <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx#TrackHET"><u>HigherEdTECH Summit</u></a> takes place Thursday, January 10.<br />
 <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />
 If wearable technology is your thing, you&rsquo;ll want to hear what <strong><strong>Christopher Nowinski</strong></strong>, Founder, President and CEO of the Sports Legacy Institute has to say about how the fitness industry is embracing technology for super-athletes and weekend warriers at the <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx#TrackFT"><u>FitnessTech</u></a> luncheon keynote at 11:40 a.m. Tuesday, January 8.<br />
 <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />
 <a href="http://cesweb.org/Conference-Program/SuperSessions.aspx"><u>The Digital Health Summit&rsquo;s SuperSession, The Next Digital Revolution</u></a><u>: Body, Mind and Soul</u>, will be moderated by <strong><strong>Arianna Huffington</strong></strong>, Editor-in-Chief of the <em>Huffington Post</em> and Creator of GPS for the Soul. Join five groundbreakers in the field of digital health as they explore what it means to be a human in the digital health revolution.<br />
 <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />
 Visit <a href="http://cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx"><u>CESweb.org</u></a> for details on all the Living in Digital Times conference tracks, including <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Conference-Program/Conference-Tracks.aspx#TrackKPMT"><u>Kids@Play and MommyTech</u></a>.</p>
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="930"><span style="display: none">“Born Mobile” – Topic of Qualcomm’s Preshow Keynote Address</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">“Born Mobile” – Topic of Qualcomm’s Preshow Keynote Address</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Keynotes/Paul-Jacobs_Qualcomm_UTTM.jpg"/>
<p>Mobile has become the largest technology platform in history and it&rsquo;s about to take center stage at the <a href="http://cesweb.org/"><u>2013 International CES&reg;.</u></a> This year&rsquo;s <a href="http://cesweb.org/Events/Keynotes.aspx"><u>preshow keynote address</u></a> will be delivered by Dr. Paul Jacobs, Chairman and CEO of Qualcomm&mdash;the world leader in mobile and connectivity technologies, and a company that was &ldquo;Born Mobile.&rdquo; Dr. Jacobs will highlight the transformative nature of mobile and the opportunities it presents for the consumer electronics industry, as well as bring on stage some very special guests. Don&rsquo;t miss this insightful and entertaining kickoff to CES, at 6:30 p.m. Monday, January 7 in The Venetian&rsquo;s Palazzo Ballroom.<br />
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
