<div class="sub-content-header">New T3 Terminal at McCarran Airport </div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Hotel%20and%20Travel%20Images/Airlines190X136.jpg"/>
<p>McCarran has a new terminal, known as T3. What does this mean for you? Terminal 1 continues to be open and operational but Terminal 2 is permanently closed. Visit <a href="https://www.mccarran.com/Fly/WhichTerminal.aspx"><u>https://www.mccarran.com/Fly/WhichTerminal.aspx</u></a> for more details.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Also at the McCarran Airport, you can pick up your badge holder before arriving on-site at CES!&nbsp; With the opening of Terminal 3 at the Las Vegas McCarran Airport, we have added both a domestic and international badge holder pickup location in the Terminal 3 Baggage Claim area. All you&rsquo;ll need to pick up your badge holder is the badge you received in the mail and two forms of ID (one business ID and one personal, photo ID). For a listing of all our badge holder pickup locations, visit <a href="http://cesweb.org/FAQ/General.aspx#jumpto3-7"><u>CESweb.org/badgeholders</u></a>.<br />
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="924"><span style="display: none">Dollar Rent a Car </span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Dollar Rent a Car </div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Hotel%20and%20Travel%20Images/Discount%20Images/17130-DOL-10-off-button.jpg"/>
<p>Dollar Rent a Car is the official car rental company for the 2013 International CES<sup>&reg;</sup>. Save ten percent during CES. Visit Dollar&rsquo;s website <a href="http://www.dollar.com/default.aspx?corpdiscnbr=CM2355"><u>www.dollar.com/default.aspx?corpdiscnbr=CM2355</u></a> to book. Discount is valid both in Las Vegas and at LAX airport.<br />
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="925"><span style="display: none">NEW! VIP Luggage Delivery Service Provided by Bags of Nevada</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">NEW! VIP Luggage Delivery Service Provided by Bags of Nevada</div><br/>

<p>This service allows you to check your luggage all the way through to your hotel or your doorstep. See <a href="http://www.maketraveleasier.com/ces2013"><u>www.MakeTravelEasier.com/ces2013</u></a> for a full list of fees and FAQ&rsquo;s.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
At the LVCC, <strong>Bags of Nevada </strong>is located in the Grand Concourse, across from Central Hall 3. Hours of operation are 8 a.m. &ndash; 5 p.m. Thursday and Friday. There is no longer a similar luggage service offered at Venetian/Palazzo.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
The best part? You can do all of this ahead of time, before you even arrive at CES! For additional information, please call Bags of Nevada on 1-877-847-0045 or visit their website <a href="http://www.maketraveleasier.com/ces2013"><u>www.MakeTravelEasier.com/ces2013</u></a><br />
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="926"><span style="display: none">Scootaround: Scooter Rental at CES</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Scootaround: Scooter Rental at CES</div><br/>

<p>Non-motorized and motorized wheel chairs are available, for a fee, to attendees during show days on a first-come, first served basis by contacting Scootaround at 888-441-7575 or by visiting&nbsp;<a href="http://www.scootaround.com/rentals/c/ces/"><u>http://www.scootaround.com/rentals/c/ces/</u></a>.<br />
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="929"><span style="display: none">Schedule Your Global Entry Interview at CES: DEADLINE EXTENDED</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Schedule Your Global Entry Interview at CES: DEADLINE EXTENDED</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/attendee/global.jpg"/>
<p>Are you a U.S. citizen who frequently travels abroad? If so, apply for the <a href="http://www.globalentry.gov/"><u>Global Entry Program</u></a> and schedule your interview at CES! Global Entry is a program that allows expedited clearance for pre-approved, low-risk travelers upon arrival in the United States.&nbsp; Participants may enter the United States by using automated kiosks located at select airports. The U.S. Customs and Border Protection Agency will be at CES January 8 and 9 to conduct interviews. To participate you must complete the application, schedule your interview at <strong>FOLA January 2013</strong> and pay the application fee by December 26. <a href="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/attendee/Global-Entry-CES.pdf">Click here </a>for complete details.<br />
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="927"><span style="display: none">Your Story</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Your Story</div><br/>

<p>No event attracts more of the world&rsquo;s technology innovators, power players and trendsetters than the 2013 International CES<sup>&reg;</sup>, and we want to hear your story!&nbsp; Email us at <a href="mailto:YourStory@CE.org"><u>YourStory@CE.org</u></a> for more information on how you can be featured in a series of CES marketing promotions!<br />
</p>
